.TH "cc_set_sram_desc" 9 "cc_set_sram_desc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cc_set_sram_desc \- Create const descriptors sequence to set values in given array into SRAM.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cc_set_sram_desc
.BI "(const u32 *src "  ","
.BI "u32 dst "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nelement "  ","
.BI "struct cc_hw_desc *seq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *seq_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "src" 12
A pointer to array of words to set as consts.
.IP "dst" 12
The target SRAM buffer to set into
.IP "nelement" 12
The number of words in "src" array
.IP "seq" 12
A pointer to the given IN/OUT descriptor sequence
.IP "seq_len" 12
A pointer to the given IN/OUT sequence length
.SH "NOTE"
each const value can't exceed word size.
